18/11/2002
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- Three candidates entered the race for Serbian president in time to meet the deadline for registration, which was Sunday (17 November). 
The candidates are Yugoslav President and Democratic Party of Serbia leader Vojislav Kostunica, Serbian Radical Party head Vojislav Seselj and the chairman of the Serbian Unity Party, Borislav Pelevic. 
The election will be held on 8 December. 
Meanwhile, Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic's Democratic Party announced that while it would not boycott the vote, it has no plans to endorse any particular candidate.
In other news, Yugoslav Foreign Minister Goran Svilanovic predicted Sunday that the country could enter the Council of Europe and NATO's Partnership for Peace programme by the middle of next year. 
Prerequisites include electing a Serbian president and reaching political consensus on a variety of issues. 
(B92, Tanjug, FoNet, BBC - 18/11/02; Tanjug, FoNet, B92 - 17/11/02)
